# Debug the Entire React + Appwrite Blog Project

A full code review of the Vite + React + Redux + Appwrite blog app revealed **12 bugs** across config, services, components, and pages.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Environment & Config

#### [MODIFY] [.env](file:///run/media/manas/New%20Volume/PROGRAMAING/Web_Devlopment/React/Project/.env)
- **Bug 1**: Typo — `VITE_APIWRITE_DATABASE_ID` should be `VITE_APPWRITE_DATABASE_ID` (notice `API` vs `APP`). This causes `config.apwriteDatabaseID` to resolve to `"undefined"`, breaking all database operations.

#### [MODIFY] [config.js](file:///run/media/manas/New%20Volume/PROGRAMAING/Web_Devlopment/React/Project/src/config/config.js)
- **Bug 2**: `apwriteDatabaseID` reads from `VITE_APIWRITE_DATABASE_ID` (typo). Fix the env var name to `VITE_APPWRITE_DATABASE_ID` to match the corrected [.env](file:///run/media/manas/New%20Volume/PROGRAMAING/Web_Devlopment/React/Project/.env).

---

### Appwrite Services

#### [MODIFY] [config.service.js](file:///run/media/manas/New%20Volume/PROGRAMAING/Web_Devlopment/React/Project/src/appwrite/config.service.js)
- **Bug 3**: `createDocument` and `updateDocument` pass `read` and `write` as top-level params — these are **not valid** in Appwrite SDK v22. They should use the `permissions` array with `Permission.read(Role.any())` etc., or be removed entirely (relying on collection-level permissions).
- **Bug 4**: [getPosts()](file:///run/media/manas/New%20Volume/PROGRAMAING/Web_Devlopment/React/Project/src/appwrite/config.service.js#88-100) accepts no parameters but the [AllPostPage](file:///run/media/manas/New%20Volume/PROGRAMAING/Web_Devlopment/React/Project/src/pages/AllPostPage.jsx#6-40) calls [getPosts([])](file:///run/media/manas/New%20Volume/PROGRAMAING/Web_Devlopment/React/Project/src/appwrite/config.service.js#88-100) — the method signature doesn't allow arguments. The internal query hardcodes `Query.equal("status", "active")` which is correct; the `[]` arg is harmless but confusing.

---

### Components

#### [MODIFY] [AuthLayout.jsx](file:///run/media/manas/New%20Volume/PROGRAMAING/Web_Devlopment/React/Project/src/components/AuthLayout.jsx)
- **Bug 5**: `import { set } from "react-hook-form"` — bogus unused import. `set` is not exported from `react-hook-form`. This will throw a build warning and is dead code. Remove it.

#### [MODIFY] [Signup.jsx](file:///run/media/manas/New%20Volume/PROGRAMAING/Web_Devlopment/React/Project/src/components/Signup.jsx)
- **Bug 6**: `import { use, useState } from "react"` — `use` is a React 19 hook but is never used in this component. Remove the unused import.

#### [MODIFY] [PostForm.jsx](file:///run/media/manas/New%20Volume/PROGRAMAING/Web_Devlopment/React/Project/src/components/post-form/PostForm.jsx)
- **Bug 7**: `import { use, useCallback, useEffect } from "react"` — same unused `use` import.
- **Bug 8**: In the [submitPost](file:///run/media/manas/New%20Volume/PROGRAMAING/Web_Devlopment/React/Project/src/components/post-form/PostForm.jsx#21-52) function (edit branch, line 23), `service.uploadFile(data.image[0])` is missing `await`. This means `file` is a Promise, not the resolved file object. `file.$id` will be `undefined`, breaking the image update flow.
- **Bug 9**: [createPost](file:///run/media/manas/New%20Volume/PROGRAMAING/Web_Devlopment/React/Project/src/appwrite/config.service.js#18-39) is called with `authorId: userData.$id` but the Appwrite collection field and the rest of the code (e.g., [PostPage.jsx](file:///run/media/manas/New%20Volume/PROGRAMAING/Web_Devlopment/React/Project/src/pages/PostPage.jsx)) uses `userId`. This field name mismatch means the author check `post.userId === userData.$id` will fail.
- **Bug 10**: `slugTransform` is called with two arguments `slugTransform(value.title, { shouldValidate: true })` on line 67 but the function only accepts one argument (`value`). The second arg `{ shouldValidate: true }` should be passed to `setValue` instead. The `setValue` call should be: `setValue("slug", slugTransform(value.title), { shouldValidate: true })`.

---

### Pages & Navigation

#### [MODIFY] [Header.jsx](file:///run/media/manas/New%20Volume/PROGRAMAING/Web_Devlopment/React/Project/src/components/header/Header.jsx)
- **Bug 11**: "All Posts" nav item points to `/posts` but the route is defined as `all-posts` in [main.jsx](file:///run/media/manas/New%20Volume/PROGRAMAING/Web_Devlopment/React/Project/src/main.jsx). Fix the path to `/all-posts`.

#### [MODIFY] [AllPostPage.jsx](file:///run/media/manas/New%20Volume/PROGRAMAING/Web_Devlopment/React/Project/src/pages/AllPostPage.jsx)
- **Bug 12**: `<PostCard post={post} />` passes a `post` prop object, but [PostCard](file:///run/media/manas/New%20Volume/PROGRAMAING/Web_Devlopment/React/Project/src/components/PostCard.jsx#5-21) destructures `{ $id, title, featuredImage }` directly. This means [PostCard](file:///run/media/manas/New%20Volume/PROGRAMAING/Web_Devlopment/React/Project/src/components/PostCard.jsx#5-21) receives `undefined` for all three props. Fix to spread the post: `<PostCard {...post} />` (matching [HomePage.jsx](file:///run/media/manas/New%20Volume/PROGRAMAING/Web_Devlopment/React/Project/src/pages/HomePage.jsx)'s pattern).

#### [MODIFY] [main.jsx](file:///run/media/manas/New%20Volume/PROGRAMAING/Web_Devlopment/React/Project/src/main.jsx)
- **Bug 13** (minor): `BrowserRouter` is imported but never used — only `createBrowserRouter` and `RouterProvider` are needed. Remove the unused import.

---

## Summary of All Fixes

| # | File | Bug | Fix |
|---|------|-----|-----|
| 1 | [.env](file:///run/media/manas/New%20Volume/PROGRAMAING/Web_Devlopment/React/Project/.env) | Typo `VITE_APIWRITE_DATABASE_ID` | Rename to `VITE_APPWRITE_DATABASE_ID` |
| 2 | [config.js](file:///run/media/manas/New%20Volume/PROGRAMAING/Web_Devlopment/React/Project/vite.config.js) | Reads wrong env var name | Change to `VITE_APPWRITE_DATABASE_ID` |
